{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3558160,"name":"","username":"Dex999999999","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dex999999999/{size}/209038_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T06:00:50.457Z","cooked":"<p>We’ve been experiencing a problem with our autos where every single path we run using a pathfollower command does not execute/carry out immediately.</p>
<p><strong>We ARE using the warmup command in RobotInit, we have tried the 0.01s waitcommand (neither seemed to make a difference?)</strong></p>
<p>For example when it scores a gamepiece in <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/ga_WJlrfpQI?feature=share" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">this video</a>, the code commands it to drive away immediately after shooting for 0.8 seconds, but it consistently waits until the elevator is almost entirely down.</p>
<p>Even at the start of auto or when driving to and from the feeder station, pauses happen that are not in our code.</p>
<p>It’s very likely we’re implementing something wrong as this is the first year we’ve tried custom autos rather than pure pathplanner but after inspecting other team’s autonomous (notably 3847, spectrum’s) our code seems to be very similar to the point where these errors don’t make sense.</p>
<p><a href="https://github.com/BCR2200/2025/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/auto/Right3Piece.java" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Here’s a snippet of our declaration of an auto:</a></p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">addCommands(
        Commands.deadline(
          new LimelightDeadline(ReefSide.BR, SnapButton.Right, 2.25),
          AutoBuildingBlocks.followPathCommand(path1)
        ),
        new LimelightAutoCmd(ReefSide.BR, e, drivetrain, SnapButton.Right, RequestState.CoralLevel4, swerve, 2),
        AutoBuildingBlocks.followPathCommand(path2),
        Commands.deadline(
          new LimelightDeadline(ReefSide.FR, SnapButton.Right, 2.25),
          AutoBuildingBlocks.followPathCommand(path3)
        ),
        new LimelightAutoCmd(ReefSide.FR, e, drivetrain, SnapButton.Right, RequestState.CoralLevel4, swerve, 2),
        AutoBuildingBlocks.followPathCommand(path4),
        Commands.deadline(
          new LimelightDeadline(ReefSide.FR, SnapButton.Left, 2.25),
          AutoBuildingBlocks.followPathCommand(path5)
          ),
        new LimelightAutoCmd(ReefSide.FR, e, drivetrain, SnapButton.Left, RequestState.CoralLevel4, swerve, 2)
    );
</code></pre>
<p><a href="https://github.com/BCR2200/2025/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/auto/AutoBuildingBlocks.java" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">and <em>our</em> followPathCommand:</a></p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public static Command followPathCommand(PathPlannerPath path) {
    RobotConfig config;
    try {
      config = RobotConfig.fromGUISettings();
    } catch (IOException | ParseException e1) {
      // TODO Auto-generated catch block
      throw new IllegalArgumentException();
    }
    return new FollowPathCommand(
        path,
        () -&gt; drivetrain.getState().Pose,
        () -&gt; drivetrain.getState().Speeds,
        (speeds, feedforwards) -&gt; drivetrain.setControl(
            drivetrain.m_pathApplyRobotSpeeds.withSpeeds(speeds)
                .withWheelForceFeedforwardsX(feedforwards.robotRelativeForcesXNewtons())
                .withWheelForceFeedforwardsY(feedforwards.robotRelativeForcesYNewtons())),
        new PPHolonomicDriveController(
            // PID constants for translation
            new PIDConstants(5, 0, 0),
            // PID constants for rotation
            new PIDConstants(7.0, 0, 0)),
        config,
        // Assume the path needs to be flipped for Red vs Blue, this is normally the
        // case
        () -&gt; Robot.alliance == Alliance.Red,
        drivetrain // Subsystem for requirements
    );
  }
</code></pre>
<p>and <a href="https://github.com/BCR2200/2025/tree/main/src/main/java/frc/robot" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">the codebase for good measure</a></p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T06:00:50.457Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":12,"reads":357,"readers_count":356,"score":206.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":495757,"topic_slug":"every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://youtube.com/shorts/ga_WJlrfpQI?feature=share","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":15},{"url":"https://github.com/BCR2200/2025/tree/main/src/main/java/frc/robot","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"2025/src/main/java/frc/robot at main · BCR2200/2025 · GitHub","clicks":2},{"url":"https://github.com/BCR2200/2025/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/auto/Right3Piece.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"2025/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/auto/Right3Piece.java at main · BCR2200/2025 · GitHub","clicks":1},{"url":"https://github.com/BCR2200/2025/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/auto/AutoBuildingBlocks.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"2025/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/auto/AutoBuildingBlocks.java at main · BCR2200/2025 · GitHub","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62784,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second/495757/1","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":3}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":3,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3558193,"name":"","username":"crueter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T11:46:15.200Z","cooked":"<p>I’m on my phone right now so I can’t do any detailed analysis, but this area would likely be your culprit (im <code>LimelightAutoCmd</code>):</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">// e movement stuff
    if (e.atFinalPosition(ep) &amp;&amp; shootTimer.get() == 0 &amp;&amp; driveAtPosition) {
      e.shootLust = true;
      shootTimer.restart();
    }
    if (e.atFinalPosition(ep) &amp;&amp; abandonTimer.get() == 0) {
      abandonTimer.restart();
    }
    // TODO adjust the value
    if (abandonTimer.get() &gt; 1.0) {
      e.shootLust = true;
    }
    if (shootTimer.get() &gt; 0.3 || abandonTimer.get() &gt; 1.5) {
      e.shootLust = false;
      e.requestState(RequestState.None);
    }

    if (shootTimer.get() &gt; 0.8 || abandonTimer.get() &gt; 2.0) {
      finished = true; // blame Adam for this brain death
    }
</code></pre>
<p>Without necessarily stepping inside each function, it looks as if it’s resetting the timer when the elevator reaches L4, meaning that it will end 0.8 seconds after the elevator reaches that point.</p>
<p>For future reference, I would highly recommend looking into <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-compositions.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Command Compositions</a> rather than C-style subroutines. It should generally create cleaner commands and make things a little simpler to debug.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T11:46:15.200Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":255,"readers_count":254,"score":61.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495757,"topic_slug":"every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-compositions.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Command Compositions — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second/495757/2","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3558200,"name":"","username":"Dex999999999","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dex999999999/{size}/209038_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T12:10:29.108Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks for the reply, but it most definitely isn’t. We’ve logged thru each step of auto and it exits LimelightAutoCmd properly, that timer is supposed to reset when the elevator is in position. It makes sure we shoot for long enough that the coral clears the wheels</p>
<p>And it doesn’t explain this</p>
